summary: 04/11/1993: Ashraf Abdallah, believed to be a member of an unknown Muslim militant group, planted five gasoline bombs on a bus carrying German tourists in Cairo. A guide saw Abdallah put a bag under a seat on the bus and called the police. Abdallah was arrested and a bomb disposal crew removed the bombs. No injuries were reported.
motive: Abdallah claimed that his militant group had assigned him to blow up tourists at the citadel in Cairo.
